Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.10,0:01:39.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,Koyomi Wind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.04,0:01:42.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,Agosto
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.67,0:01:48.54,HnF,,0,0,0,,Principios de Agosto
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.14,0:01:53.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,P-Perdona la intromisión, Koyomi.{S-Sorry to intrude, Koyomi-onii-chan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.04,0:01:57.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,Oh, bienvenida Sengoku, pasa.{ Oh, you're here, Sengoku. Come in.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.06,0:02:00.53,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ahora que lo pienso, mejor me voy, no tengo nada que hacer aquí.{Ahora que lo pienso, no debería haber venido,\N me volveré a casa.}{Now that I think about it, I shouldn’t be intruding, so I’ll go back home.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.53,0:02:02.58,HnF,,0,0,0,,No te vayas justo después de entrar.{Don’t go back the second you make a visit.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.52,0:02:06.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,A-Adiós. Ha sido divertido.{G-g-goodbye. I had fun today.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.90,0:02:08.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡No te vayas!{ There’s no way you did!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.61,0:02:09.65,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es...{I…}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.65,0:02:11.65,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es el mejor día de mi vida.{ It was the best day of my life.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.97,0:02:16.74,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eh... ¿exactamente que te divierte de la entrada de mi casa?{You... what exactly is fun about the entrance of the Araragi household?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.74,0:02:18.38,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Y por qué el mejor día?{¿Y se supone que eres un "maestro de la vida"?}{And are you supposed to be a master of life!?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.51,0:02:20.95,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Fue en principios de Agosto.{It was early August.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.95,0:02:24.37,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,El día en el que se resolvió\N cierto incidente de un estafador.{On that day the incident of a certain con man was resolved.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.37,0:02:27.06,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Vino a mi casa Sengoku Nadeko.{Sengoku Nadeko, came to visit my house.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.64,0:02:31.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,Igualmente, pasa. Ya está todo preparado.{Anyway, come on in.  I've made all the preparations for entertainment.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.04,0:02:33.67,HnF,,0,0,0,,Hoy habrá una gran fiesta{que durará hasta la noche}.{Today, it’ll be a party that lasts through the night!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.10,0:02:41.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque se suponía que iba a venir Tsukihi...{Realmente, se suponía que Tsukihi iba a estar con nosotros también...}{To be honest, Tsukihi-chan was also supposed to be with us…}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.14,0:02:46.38,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero parece que tiene que limpiar algo{hacer algún trabajo de limpieza}.{But it seems she has some clean-up work to do again.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.38,0:02:49.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Eh? ¿Qué tipo de limpieza?{Ah, clean-up work? What kind?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.72,0:02:52.48,HnF,,0,0,0,,Lo que pasó con ese estafador.{Cleaning up after that con man.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.06,0:03:00.94,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es verdad, es una fiesta. La has preparado bien.{ It’s true. It’s a party, you set up a party!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.52,0:03:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(483,510)}¿Existe algún tipo de costumbre de quitarte los calcetines cuando entras en la habitación de otra persona?{ Was there any manners along the lines of taking off your socks when you entered someone else's room?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.92,0:03:19.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y-Ya sé que Tsukihi no vendrá,\N pero, ¿Karen tampoco?{I.. I know Tsukihi-chan is out, but what about Karen-san?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.78,0:03:24.10,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sí. Esas dos van juntas siempre, son un conjunto.{Yeah. Those two are a set, after all. They’re sold as a package deal.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.26,0:03:27.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Y... tus padres?{And… your parents?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.68,0:03:31.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,Están fuera también, están trabajando.{My parents are out too, that is, they're at work.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.38,0:03:40.14,HnF,,0,0,0,,E-Entonces...ahora mismo... estamos los dos solos...{Th-then, today it’s just Nadeko and \NKoyomi-onii-chan, just the two of us.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.40,0:03:45.71,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, supongo que sí. ¿Algún problema?{Well, I guess it is just the two of us. Is there something about that?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.71,0:03:47.74,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, no pasa nada.{Of course there’s no problem with it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.80,0:03:53.91,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces... Bienvenida, Sengoku.{Well, first of all. Welcome, Sengoku!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.91,0:03:58.05,HnF,,0,0,0,,Gracias Koyomi.{Y-yes! Thank you, Koyomi-onii-chan!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.05,0:03:58.91,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Brindemos!{ Cheers!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.88,0:04:01.70,HnF,,0,0,0,,Feliz cumpleaños.{Happy birthday!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.98,0:04:04.49,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Mi cumpleaños fue en Abril.{My birthday was in April.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.37,0:04:10.90,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Acabé de contarle a Sengoku todo lo que sabía sobre el caso del estafador.{I finished telling Sengoku all I could regarding the case of the con man.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.96,0:04:16.81,HnF,,0,0,0,,Koyomi, en mi caso es obvio...{Koyomi-onii-chan? In my case it’s obvious…}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.81,0:04:22.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero, ¿cómo divulgó exactamente esos rumores el estafador?{But how exactly did Mister Con Man spread those rumors?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.10,0:04:30.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,Los rumores... los encantamientos... o las historias de fantasmas.{The rumors… or the charms… or the ghost stories.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.47,0:04:33.37,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Cómo? Eso fue...{The way he did it? That is-}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.25,0:04:36.29,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Leyendas urbanas,{Urban legends,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.29,0:04:37.71,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,cotilleos,{Street gossip,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:39.34,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,rumores.{Rumors.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.34,0:04:42.80,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Divulgándolos no como oyente, sino como orador.{Spreading them not as the listener but the speaker.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.80,0:04:45.84,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,¿Qué hizo exactamente para conseguir eso?{What specifically did you have to do to do that?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:49.65,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,¿Cómo se las arregló ese estafador para divulgar esos rumores?{That con man, how did he manage to spread those rumors?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.47,0:04:53.23,HnF,,0,0,0,,En primer lugar, ¿quién fue el primero que esparció esos rumores?{In the first place, who did everyone hear those rumors from?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.76,0:04:56.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No fue directamente el estafador?{Not from the con man himself?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:04:59.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,Todos decían lo mismo.{Everyone around me said this.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.02,0:05:02.14,HnF,,0,0,0,,Rumores en el viento.{Rumors in the wind, they said.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.44,0:05:05.28,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,¿En el viento?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:12.60,HnF,,0,0,0,,El proceso por el que los rumores se esparcen.{The process by which rumors spread.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.33,0:05:15.65,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿O es el proceso por el que alguien los esparce?{Or is it the process by which one spreads rumors?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.57,0:05:19.45,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Cómo pudo ese estafador\N conseguir propagar esos rumor?{How exactly did that con man manage to pull something like that off?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.97,0:05:28.75,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si yo quisiese hacer circular\N algún rumor, usaría a Tsukihi.{ If I wanted to circulate some kind of rumor… Then I would rely on Tsukihi-chan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.75,0:05:34.60,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ella es bastante conocida entre las chicas de secundaria, así que si le contase un rumor,{She’s a celebrity among middle school girls, so if I tell the influential Tsukihi-chan a rumor,}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.60,0:05:39.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,sería lo mismo que contárselo a cien personas.{then it would be almost the same as telling a hundred people.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.50,0:05:44.81,HnF,,0,0,0,,No creo que el estafador usase esos métodos.{…I think that the con man probably didn’t use the methods we just talked about}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.81,0:05:46.63,HnF,,0,0,0,,{\pos(483,510)}Es más probable que hubiese planeado que el rumor se propagase de 'amigo a amigo'.{It’s actually more likely that he planned it for a person like that to be told from a 'friend of a friend’.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.42,0:05:50.70,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque tal vez suene contradictorio...{Even though it sounds contradictory…}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.70,0:05:54.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,Algo que se pudiese propagar sin anunciarlo o sin tener que hacer nada.{Something that can spread without advertising or publicity or any action whatsoever.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.41,0:05:57.62,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sería el virus ideal.{That’s what the ideal virus would be.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.08,0:06:02.25,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero... si simplemente esperas que algo se propague por su cuenta...{ But… If you just expect something to spread on its own...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:04.51,HnF,,0,0,0,,Algo más espontáneo...{Something more spontaneous…}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.51,0:06:07.45,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No estás esperando una coincidencia?{Aren't you just waiting for coincidence?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.68,0:06:16.20,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y ahora, el epílogo, o mejor, la conclusión.{And now for the epilogue, or rather, the punch line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.66,0:06:23.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,El poder de leer el viento, el poder de controlarlo.{The power to read the wind, the power to raise the wind.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:26.11,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eso no existe{Yo no tengo tal cosa.}{}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.11,0:06:30.05,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque también puede que eso sea mentira.{que te esté mintiendo.}{Although, it’s possible that that’s a lie.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.53,0:06:37.33,HnF,,0,0,0,,No obstante, el poder de leer el viento\N no es muy importante realmente,{However, if you ask me, the power to read the wind isn’t very important in the first place,}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.33,0:06:42.96,HnF,,0,0,0,,porque para una pandemia,\N lo más importante es la falta de viento.{because for pandemics, the most important is a windless condition.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.43,0:06:45.29,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Falta de viento?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.29,0:06:50.60,HnF,,0,0,0,,Que algo sea popular, \Nsignifica que hay algo que no lo es.{When something’s popular, it means that something else isn’t popular.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.11,0:06:57.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,En esta ciudad en concreto, no podía poner un pie durante las vacaciones de primavera.{About this town specifically, I couldn’t lay a hand here during spring break.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:07:02.61,HnF,,0,0,0,,Porque el chisme sobre el 'vampiro' se estaba extendiendo.{Because the gossip about the 'vampire’ was sweeping over.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.61,0:07:07.36,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero una vez que el rumor se acabó, en un lugar vacío de rumores,{So once that rumor died out in a completely empty location,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.36,0:07:10.95,HnF,,0,0,0,,en un lugar con hambre de chismorreos, lancé mis propios rumores.{in a location that was starving, I plunged my own rumors in.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.40,0:07:13.62,HnF,,0,0,0,,Historias de fantasmas, cotilleos, leyendas urbanas.{Ghost stories, street gossip, urban legends.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:17.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,Cuando el corazón está descuidado, es cuando se esparcen rápidamente esos rumores.{It’s when the human heart is in disarray that these baseless rumors run rampant.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:22.64,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y el corazón está descuidado, principalmente, cuando no tienen nada en lo que apoyarse.{When I say the human heart is in disarray, basically, there isn’t anything to rely on.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.13,0:07:30.11,HnF,,0,0,0,,Piensa en qué sujetos\N podría interesarse un estafador.{Think about what kind of lame ducks a con man might want to target.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.11,0:07:31.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,No quiero pensar en algo como eso.{I don’t even want to think about something like that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.57,0:07:36.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, eso sería... ¿los ricos?\N¿No irían a por alguien con mucho dinero?{Well, that would be… The wealthy? Don’t they go for the rich?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.04,0:07:37.37,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eso es lo que pensarían las buenas personas.{That would be what good people think.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.37,0:07:41.10,HnF,,0,0,0,,Alguien que ya está satisfecho es difícil de engañar.{Someone who’s already satisfied is hard to deceive.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:47.19,HnF,,0,0,0,,Las personas con superávit en su cuentas\N son personas con superávit en sus corazones.{Humans with a surplus in their lives are humans with a surplus in their hearts.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.19,0:07:51.70,HnF,,0,0,0,,Por eso la gente buscada por un estafador, son los insatisfechos,{That’s why the people that con men target are the dissatisfied,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.70,0:07:54.58,HnF,,0,0,0,,la gente con déficit en el corazón.{the humans without a surplus in their hearts.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.30,0:07:59.62,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Es por eso que cuando viniste a esta ciudad fuiste a por los niños de secundaria?{That’s why, when you came to this town, you went for the middle school girls?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.40,0:08:06.38,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es probable. Los corazones repletos de ansiedad, son fáciles de seducir.{I suppose. Hearts filled with anxiety are easy to deceive.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.38,0:08:10.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,Porque incluso si están llenos de mentiras, no tienen la libertad para comprobarlo.{Because even if they’re possessed with lies, they don’t have the freedom to verify them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.11,0:08:19.64,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tu has dicho que para mi plan, vendía 'amuletos' que deterioraban las relaciones humanas.{You said that, for my plan, I spread the 'charms’ to cause the deterioration of human relations.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:22.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero es al contrario.{But it’s actually the opposite.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.56,0:08:27.85,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es porque las relaciones estaban deterioradas, que todos iban a comprar mis 'amuletos'.{Because human relations were deteriorating, everyone jumped for my 'charms’.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.34,0:08:31.11,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Estás diciendo que es culpa suya el ser engañados?{Are you saying it’s their fault for being tricked?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.11,0:08:34.91,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si lo dices así, se podría decir que sí.{When you say it like that, I want to agree.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.91,0:08:37.91,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tal vez deba decir que la generación estaba mal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.91,0:08:44.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si te preguntas por qué algo como esto es popular, para poder discutir el desorden en las personas,{'Why is something like this so popular?’ If you want to discuss a chaotic state like that,}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.00,0:08:47.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,debes preguntarte primero\N el espacio en blanco antes del caos.{you should first discuss the blank space before the chaos.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.68,0:08:48.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,Espacio en blanco.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.16,0:08:51.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,La oscuridad podrías decir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.88,0:08:53.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,Por eso te daré este gran consejo:{That’s why I’ll give you this piece of advice:}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.97,0:08:59.43,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si algo que es 'completamente incomprensible' comienza a ser popular, sospecha de tu generación.{If 'something that is utterly incomprehensible’ starts getting popular, doubt your generation.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.43,0:09:01.93,HnF,,0,0,0,,Piensa que algo podría estar muy mal.{Consider that something might be very wrong.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.93,0:09:06.55,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eso podría ser porque la generación\N ha sido envuelta por la oscuridad.{That's because the generation has been enveloped by darkness.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.60,0:09:09.66,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Envuelta por la oscuridad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.06,0:09:13.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y ahora, Araragi,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.49,0:09:21.37,HnF,,0,0,0,,ahora que te he contado un secreto tan importante para mí, aceptaría encantado un honorario.{Now that I’ve taught you a very important trade secret of mine, why don’t I accept a fee from you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.37,0:09:23.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sospecho que el dinero que guardas para situaciones especiales,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.50,0:09:26.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,está en el bolsillo interior de tu chaqueta. {My guess is that the money you kept for a crucial moment is in the inner pocket of your jacket.}
